description: Dishes can be fleeting, because Sanford serves a seasonal menu and has, long before it was cool.
Ardent, with its changing tasting menu of 10 or so courses, always surprises and delights.
You never know what you’ll get on the tasting menu by chefs Dan Jacobs and Dan Van Rite but it assuredly will be delicious.
Combinations might surprise, like last fall’s gnocchi with Concord grape, but they’re bound to please.
Seafood includes everything from oysters (raw or chargrilled) to rich preparations for lobster. Expect modern cocktails and a number of boutique wines from the bar.
The lighthearted modern French restaurant with a bouncy ’70s soundtrack, is making a splash just a few months after opening.
Story Hill BKC is destination dining. You’re visiting? Go. You’re new to Milwaukee? Go. You love good food? Go!
Twenty-five years look good on you, Ristorante. You’re still the standard-bearer of traditional Italian cuisine.
Chef de cuisine John Raymond is serving powerfully delicious French-inflected plates these days.
The restaurant, operated by chefs Dan Jacobs and Dan Van Rite and led in the kitchen by chef de cuisine Kristen Schwab, takes a modern approach to American Chinese food.
The soups, salads and sandwiches at Amaranth feel so wholesome that it’s easy to justify dessert.

It serves a few Japanese, Korean and American Chinese plates, but most of the extensive menu is traditional Chinese fare — so traditional that it draws the international students studying in Milwaukee who are seeking a taste of home.
The Friday-to-Sunday restaurant sometimes can sell out of food as early as noon, especially on Sundays.

You might think the best thing about the weekend is the not-working part, but it’s actually the specials at Chilango Express, especially the roast lamb the restaurant sells by the pound with fresh, handmade tortillas.
Local ingredients are favored for flavors that go global.
The platter that’s brought to the table, bearing the large sourdough flatbread that’s topped with entrées, looks like an artist’s palette.
So the menu varies by days of the week, African some days, Jamaican others, and some of each on Saturdays.
Iron Grate has grown so much that this year chef Aaron Patin got a new smoker, named Hank.
The long menu at Kim’s Thai has all your Thai favorites — plus some dishes that could become favorites, if only you try them.
Ideas for dishes are global, like Peruvian tacu tacu, a bean and rice cake embellished with poblano sauce, avocado salad and tortilla chip “dust”.
